  "prompt": "What language was spoken in the period of Lord Rama?",
  "response": "The period of Lord Rama, as described in the Ramayana, is traditionally believed to be set in ancient India, which would correspond to a time when early forms of languages spoken in the Indian subcontinent were developing. The language most commonly associated with this era in the context of the Ramayana is Sanskrit, as the epic itself was composed in Sanskrit. Additionally, various Prakrit languages, which are derived from Sanskrit and were spoken in different regions, may also have been in use during that time. However, since the Ramayana is a mythological text, the exact linguistic landscape of Lord Rama's era remains a matter of interpretation and scholarly debate.",
